<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>530 and DT-466/408 Diesel Engine Service (1994) - TIMING GEAR TRAIN AND FRONT COVER - ENGINE GEAR TRAIN
        TIMING
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>ENGINE GEAR TRAIN TIMING</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="5">
            <title>INSTALLATION Idler Gear Assemblies</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the crankcase front cover (rear half) as follows:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install a new front cover O-ring into the groove in the cover. Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050828">8.28</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        .
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Mount the front cover to the crankcase using nine bolts. Tighten the bolts to the
                        special torque value. Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk document="e105_180.xml" xrefid="ef1050826">8.26</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        .
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new crankshaft gear and oil spline gear, if required, as specified in Section
                    7.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reinstall the crankshaft. Refer to Section 7 for installation instructions.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If required, press on a new camshaft gear as explained in Section 5.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the camshaft and gear assembly as specified in Section 5.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Check camshaft end play and be sure the tappets move freely in their bores.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <figure id="ef1050828" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg2459" filename="../figeg2/eg2459.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 8.28.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Front Cover</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the lower idler gear as follows: (Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050829">8.29</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install the gear with the timing marks facing out.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Tighten the retaining bolt to the special torque value.</para>
                    <specpara>
                        <important>
                            <para>REMEASURE CRANKSHAFT TO IDLER GEAR BACKLASH, AFTER INSTALLATION TO CONFIRM PROPER
                                REASSEMBLY.
                            </para>
                        </important>
                    </specpara>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the upper idler gear as follows: (Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050830">8.30</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <important>
                        <para>A NEW UPPER IDLER GEAR BOLT MUST BE USED TO AT EACH INSTALLATION OF UPPER IDLER GEAR.
                        </para>
                    </important>
                </specpara>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install the gear with the timing marks facing out.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Tighten the retaining bolt to the special torque value.</para>
                    <figure id="ef1050829" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg2460" filename="../figeg2/eg2460.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 8.29.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. Lower Idler Gear</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. Crankshaft</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. Mounting Bolt</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="ef1050830" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg2461" filename="../figeg2/eg2461.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 8.30.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. Camshaft Gear</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. Upper Idler Gear</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. Lower Idler Gear</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">When an engine has been disassembled and the camshaft, crankshaft or idler gear removed,
                    the gears must be assembled with the timing marks properly aligned, as shown in
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050831">8.31</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>The single punch marks on the crankshaft and lower idler gear and camshaft and upper idler
                            gear must align, while the two punch marks on both the idler gears must align.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Once assembled at "marks aligned" position, engine will require 37 crankshaft revolutions
                            for "marks aligned" position again.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <specpara>
                    <important>
                        <para>REMEASURE CAMSHAFT TO IDLER GEAR AFTER INSTALLATION TO CONFIRM PROPER REASSEMBLY.</para>
                    </important>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the fuel pump drive gear in position, with the machined side towards the outside
                    (front) of engine. The gear has 5 kidney-shaped holes. Three holes are grouped together and the
                    middle hole should be placed in the 10 o'clock position.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">. Install the oil pressure relief valve into the front cover (rear half). Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050832">8.32</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <figure id="ef1050831" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg2454" filename="../figeg2/eg2454.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 8.31.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Camshaft Gear</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Upper Idler Gear</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. Fuel Pump Gear</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. Crankshaft Gear</callout1>
                        <callout1>5. Lower Idler Gear</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1050832" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg2455" filename="../figeg2/eg2455.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 8.32.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Oil Pressure Relief Valve</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Front Cover Rear Half</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
